SIMPLE: honeymoon
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Honeymoon
<hw>Hon"ey*moon`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
first month after marriage.</def> <rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A vacation taken together by a newly married couple,
usually including a trip away from home.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <mark>[fig.]</mark> <def>Any
initial period of harmony after two or more people or organizations
begin working together; <as>as, the usual <ex>honeymoon</ex> for a newly
elected president was cut short by resumption of partisan sniping over
the budget</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Honey-mouthed</ent>⟦br⟧
